-- Canada's Telus withdraws Mobilicity bid, newspaper says
-- By Alastair Sharp
-- Wed May 21, 2014 12:09PM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, May 21 (Reuters) - Canada's Telus Corp <T.TO> has withdrawn its bid to acquire struggling domestic wireless company Mobilicity, the Globe and Mail newspaper reported on Wednesday, citing a source it did not identify.

The Western Canada-focused telecom company has made several bids for the much-smaller company, formally known as Data & Audio-Visual Enterprises Wireless Inc, despite federal government opposition. [ID:nL2N0NH20K] Telus, Mobilicity and court-appointed supervisors of the corporate restructuring weren't immediately available for comment.